<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF110-446-619  </DOCNO><DOCID>10 446 619.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Sept 14 1990 n1512* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Inmos offers transputer module with general purpose interface bus.andO;(IMS B421 connects General Purpose Interface Bus to networks oftransputers) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   INMOS International PLC (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Inmos IMS B421 (Integrated circuit) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionIntegrated Circuits.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>INMOS OFFERS TRANSPUTER MODULE WITH GENERAL PURPOSEandM;INTERFACE BUSandM;Inmos International Plc, now owned by Franco-Italian SGS-ThomsonMicroelectronics Group BV, has added to its range of modular hardware andsoftware blocks for creating scalable end-user systems.andP;  The IMS B421, aninterface Transputer module, provides a bridge between the General PurposeInterface Bus and the Transputer.andP;  The General Purpose Interface Bus definesa means of interconnecting instruments to form a system around which data andcontrol information can be passed, and it is the most common name for theIEEE-488 standard.andP;  The IMS B421 measures 4&quot; by 3&quot; and combines an IEEE-488interface with a 20MHz IMS T222 16-bit Transputer, 48Kb of two-cycle staticrandom access memory and 8Kb of electrically erasable read only memory.andP;  Theinterface chip is sourced from Texas Instruments, and the Transputer moduleis designed for ICL and IBM-compatible motherboards.andP;  A software package, theF001, is supplied with the B421, and it provides support for the datatransfer requirements of IEEE-488.1.andP;  When the Transputer module and F001software are used together, IEEE-488 test and instrumentation systems may bedirectly connected to networks of transputers.andP;  The software package providesa means of access to the B421 via library calls, and is designed to performmost of the General Purpose In-terface Bus handling.andP;  Inmos says that theB421 may be embedded in an instrument and carry out processing and controltasks, or it can convey arrays of data to networked Transputers forhigh-speed processing.andP;  Characteristics of the General Purpose Interface Buscan be user-defined so that the Transputer can act as a system or non-systemcontroller.andP;  The IMS B421 is available from Inmos and SGS-ThomsonMicroelectronics, and it costs around #870.andO;</TEXT></DOC>